      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.1101/2025.01.18.25320755"
      },
      "sc:description": "jaxQTL is a flexible and efficient sc-eQTL mapping framework using count-based models, designed to analyze sparse counts in scRNA-seq data and large datasets. It has been shown to identify more eGenes compared with existing approaches, improving our ability to identify distal eQTLs.",
